# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next Q4_1 on 2x R9700 (MACHINE=r9700-dual).
#
# Sourced by run-vulkan.sh AFTER models/qwen3-coder-next-q4.env and BEFORE
# profiles/r9700-dual/default.env, so the values here win over the card default
# but the CLI/env still win over these. Holds only what depends on THIS model's
# weights fitting on THIS GPU pair -- nothing model-intrinsic (that's in
# models/qwen3-coder-next-q4.env) and nothing card-generic (that's in default.env).
#
# Target: the model's native 256K max context, all weights in VRAM. Q4_1 is
# ~47.3 GiB; this model has only 2 KV heads (aggressive GQA) so even 256K KV is
# modest. The three knobs below are tuned together to make 256K FIT -- do not
# change one in isolation:
#   - CTX_SIZE=262144: the model's full context_length.
#   - UBATCH=512: shrinks the per-GPU compute buffer from ~3-5 GiB (at 2048) to
#     ~1-1.5 GiB. This is the main lever keeping 256K under the VRAM ceiling.
#   - CACHE_TYPE_V=q4_0: drops KV from ~13.6 to ~10.5 GiB. K stays q8_0 (launcher
#     default) for quality; flash-attn is on by default, which quantized V needs.
# Budget: ~47.3 GiB weights + ~10.5 GiB KV + ~1.5 GiB compute ~= 59 GiB / 62 GiB.
# The margin is ~3 GiB. If load OOMs: drop UBATCH to 256, then lower CTX_SIZE.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=262144}"
: "${UBATCH:=512}"
: "${CACHE_TYPE_V:=q4_0}"
